  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (6d6f854 2023-06-19T00:07:11.657015827Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge script script/Deploy.s.sol --mnemonics 1 --mnemonic-indexes 1 --ledger --broadcast  --rpc-url $RPC_URL\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nusing ` --mnemonics 1` when running a script gives the following error: the word `1` is invalid\r\n\r\nI aim to run a script with the 1st derivation on my ledger.\r\n\r\nIt was running well before the new forge version (for example, check the usage on [morpho-labs/safer](https://github.com/morpho-labs/safer/tree/main#hardware-wallet-support))",
