    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@Evalir not 100% sure if it's the same issue, but i saw this pop up a few times on telegram as well.\r\n\r\nThe issue seems to be that until recently, when using ledger `--broadcast --ledger --mnemonic-indexes ${MNEMONIC_INDEX} --sender ${LEDGER_SENDER}` would have worked perfectly fine.\r\n\r\nThen some update was made on foundry: `--mnemonics` was suddenly required(but ignored, when using m-index & sender), so ppl started using `--broadcast --ledger --mnemonic-indexes ${MNEMONIC_INDEX} --sender ${LEDGER_SENDER} --mnemonics 1`.\r\n\r\nIn another update `--mnemonics` validation seems to have been changed, so `1` is no longer valid. We use `--mnemonics foo` as a workaround, which seems to satisfy validation.\r\n\r\nThe core issue seems to be that this is required, even when not used.",
